      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# 🍳 MiseFlow 1.0.5 — Initial public release\r\n\r\n> *Mise en place* — the culinary practice of preparing everything before you cook.\r\n\r\nMiseFlow turns your Obsidian recipe notes into a full meal planning and grocery system. This is the first public release.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n**Meal planning**\r\n- Add recipes to your weekly plan with an optional day and meal type\r\n- Choose exactly which ingredients to add to your grocery list — nothing is added blindly\r\n- Your meal plan lives in a real vault note you can edit by hand\r\n\r\n**Grocery list**\r\n- Note-backed: stored as a readable Markdown checklist you can edit directly\r\n- Smart quantity merging across recipes and manually added items\r\n- Group by category, by recipe, by source, or as a flat list\r\n- Add one-off items not tied to any recipe\r\n- Export as plain text, Markdown checklist, or grouped by category\r\n\r\n**Shopping Assistant panel**\r\n- Check off items as you shop — state syncs to the grocery note\r\n- See meals planned for the week with a link to the meal plan note\r\n- Reset checks between trips\r\n\r\n**Recipe view**\r\n- Clean card view for cooking: hero image, portion multiplier, timing badges, diet tags, nutrition panel\r\n- Meat temperature safety badges on relevant ingredients\r\n- Allergen warning banner if a recipe matches your personal allergen list\r\n- Optional high-GI ingredient badges with a configurable dictionary\r\n- Mark as cooked (records date and increments cook count in frontmatter)\r\n- Add to meal plan directly from the recipe view\r\n\r\n**Recipe library**\r\n- Meal suggester surfaces recipes you haven't cooked recently\r\n- Cooking stats leaderboard\r\n- Favourite recipes with one click\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Bug fixes in this release\r\n- Fixed meat temperature badge stretching to full width in the recipe view\r\n- Fixed cramped layout in the Add to meal plan modal\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nIf you run into anything unexpected, please [open an issue](https://github.com/ATommasi/miseflow/issues).\r\n",
